                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/39772",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=php4dev",
                        "name": "php4dev",
                        "displayName": "PHP4Dev",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "I agree totaly.\r\nThe class is declared in Zend\/View\/Helper\/Navigation\/Menu.php in line 425.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=php4dev",
                        "name": "php4dev",
                        "displayName": "PHP4Dev",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2010-04-03T05:07:05.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2010-04-03T05:07:05.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/41749",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=sugoi",
                        "name": "sugoi",
                        "displayName": "Maurice Bonemeijer",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "I agree as well.\r\n\r\nSome situations where an id would be desired:\r\n* in many cases it's more efficient to write css selectors based on id\r\n* certain js menu's out there rely on id\r\n\r\nI would expect setting an id on a navigation container would be part of the most basic features.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=sugoi",
                        "name": "sugoi",
                        "displayName": "Maurice Bonemeijer",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2010-07-27T02:40:25.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2010-07-27T02:40:25.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/44207",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=kaiuwe",
                        "name": "kaiuwe",
                        "displayName": "Kai Uwe",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "The patch should include the following points:\r\n\r\n* use [Zend_View_Helper_Navigation_HelperAbstract::_htmlAttribs()|http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/apidoc\/core\/Zend_View\/Helper\/Zend_View_Helper_Navigation_HelperAbstract.html#_htmlAttribs]\r\n* use [Zend_View_Helper_HtmlElement::_normalizeId()|http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/apidoc\/core\/Zend_View\/Helper\/Zend_View_Helper_HtmlElement.html#_normalizeId]\r\n\r\n{code:title=Excerpt from Zend_View_Helper_Navigation_Menu}\r\n\/\/ start new ul tag\r\nif ($ulClass && $depth ==  0) {\r\n    $ulClass = ' class=\"' . $ulClass . '\"';\r\n} else {\r\n    $ulClass = '';\r\n}\r\n$html .= $myIndent . '<ul' . $ulClass . '>' . self::EOL;\r\n{code}\r\n\r\n{code:title=Improvement}\r\n$attribs = array();\r\n\r\n\/\/ start new ul tag\r\nif (0 == $depth) {\r\n    $attribs = array(\r\n        'class' => $ulClass,\r\n        'id'    => $ulId,\r\n    );\r\n}\r\n\r\n$html .= $myIndent . '<ul'\r\n                   . $this->_htmlAttribs($attribs)\r\n                   . '>'\r\n                   . self::EOL;\r\n{code}\r\nZend_View_Helper_HtmlElement::_htmlAttribs() uses the method \"_normalizeId\"!\r\n{code:title=Excerpt from Zend_View_Helper_Navigation_HelperAbstract}\r\nprotected function _normalizeId($value)\r\n{\r\n    $prefix = get_class($this);\r\n    $prefix = strtolower(trim(substr($prefix, strrpos($prefix, '_')), '_'));\r\n\r\n    return $prefix . '-' . $value;\r\n}\r\n{code}\r\n\r\n{code:title=Improvement}\r\nprotected function _normalizeId($value)\r\n{        \r\n    \/\/ ... no hard coded prefix (@see ZF-10409)\r\n\r\n    return parent::_normalizeId($value);\r\n}\r\n{code}\r\n\r\nSee also ZF-10409",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=kaiuwe",
                        "name": "kaiuwe",
                        "displayName": "Kai Uwe",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2011-01-28T09:51:45.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2011-01-28T09:51:45.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/44583",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=skors",
                        "name": "skors",
                        "displayName": "Sebastian Kors",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Hi,\r\n\r\nit's easy to use your own view helper which adds an id for example.\r\n\r\njust create your own view helper class which extends Zend_View_Helper_Navigation_HelperAbstract or Zend_View_Helper_Navigation_Menu and overwrite or replace the mentioned parts.\r\n\r\nuse your own view helper as follows:\r\n\r\n\/\/ in your view- or layout script\r\n<?php echo $this->navigation()->findHelper('Navigation_MyOwnMenu')->myOwnMenu()->mySetIdMethod('mymenuid')->setUlClass('fancyclass') ; ?>\r\n\r\ndont forget to add your library in application.ini for example, so it finds your own view helper.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=skors",
                        "name": "skors",
                        "displayName": "Sebastian Kors",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2011-02-25T15:05:12.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2011-02-25T15:05:12.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/46793",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=kaiuwe",
                        "name": "kaiuwe",
                        "displayName": "Kai Uwe",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "The patch fixes ZF-7212 and the subtask ZF-10409, because the new function for setting an ID uses the normalization of the ID attribute.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=kaiuwe",
                        "name": "kaiuwe",
                        "displayName": "Kai Uwe",
